<p>How do you check a <strong>radio button</strong> in an HTML page that is loaded in a web view?</p>  <p><strong>example:</strong> </p>  <p>I have two radio buttons embedded in an HTML page:</p>  <ol> <li>Allow All</li> <li>Restrict Access</li> </ol>  <p>I want to construct an app wherein if a <strong>UIButton</strong> or <strong>UISwitch</strong> is tapped, the program will automatically select <strong>"Restrict Access"</strong> and print the selection to console. </p>  <p>New to Xcode and Swift programming here.</p>  <p>using <strong>Xcode7</strong>, <strong>Swift 2.0</strong></p>